  "page_number": 18,
  "context": "18 or patented. In application, a Professor required to have a mandatory research WL of 6 must have at least 2 research studies.\n\nSection 32 On extension, short-term training/seminar shall be given 1-unit equivalent WL while long-term extension projects shall have an equivalent WL of 3 units. A short-term extension activity ranges from 6 months and below. A long-term extension activity is from seven (7) months and above. In case of no workload release, the extensionist(s) shall received cash incentive(s) subject to usual accounting and auditing rules and regulations shall be divided.\n\nSection 33 Special courses offered upon request of students and agreed to be handled by a faculty even without remuneration must not be included as a WL/TL.\n\nSection 34 In case of budget constraints, the teaching personnel who render services in excess of the regular teaching load or outside of the regular office hours may be paid in a form of non-monetary remuneration pursuant to existing Civil Service rules and regulations, provided that he/she is informed and has given prior consent and approval as to the mode of compensation. The Human Resource Management Office shall facilitate the preparation of the Affidavit of Undertaking.\n\nSection 35 Faculty members without designations handling courses in specific programs, as provided in their respective programs, standards, and guidelines (PSG), shall be allowed not more than thirty-six (36) teaching hours per week and shall receive corresponding remuneration for the teaching overload.\n\n35.1 Full-time faculty members may carry a combined RLE and classroom load of not more than thirty-six (36) hours per week which include consultation hours and other activities related to RLE instruction, research and extension (CMO 15, s.2017).\n\n35.2 The Dean and the Department Chair/Head may be allowed to handle a maximum teaching load of not more than 12 hours a week provided that their primary duties and responsibilities are not neglected.",
